data.meta_description: The Central African CFA Franc is the currency of six independent states in Central Africa who have unified to form 1 single currency to be used among all member states. Central African States - Equatorial Guinea 500 Francs, 2002. The banknote is colored in brown and white. Its obverse side depicts children learning in a classroom. Its reverse side portrays a woman in a village. Available at www.banknoteworld.com SKU: CASC506FCU #CFA #CentralAfrica #Africa #Banknote #PaperMoney
